<br>
1)  Fire Pet DS -- Why the heck doesn't the DS come naturally on the fire pet when we summon them?  It's sooooooo sooooo annoying when I have to sit around forever and wait for the fire pet to cast the DS on itself.  I have had to wait up to 15 minutes one time.  Why would I waste mana casting a DS on my fire pet when the DS is supposed to be natural?<br>
<br>
2)  Air pet invis -- Conversely, why the heck does the air pet cast invis as soon as it gets summoned?? I'm trying to give the stupid pet some weapons and armor, and it has to go invis causing me to mem ANOTHER spell and waste MORE mana and time.   Does anyone know any way to make it go un-invis?  Or is there a way to target the pet and give it the items when it is invis?  Why are pets made to be inconvenient?  We should be able to tell the fire pet to DS itself and we should be able to tell the air pet to un-invis itself.<br>
<br>
3)  I know I spoke about this before, but I feel it shoudl be stressed again and was wondering what everyone else's opinions about this was...Why...why why why do our pets still disappear when we go LD?  If they don't aggro anymore, why is it necessary for me to waste 20 minutes re-summoning it and all the stuff I give it each time I LD.  So inconvenient.<br>
<br>
