This has been explained before.  Fire (and epic) pets take a while to DS themselves because of all the pets in the game that the world servers have to track.  Try making a pet during off-peak hours (like in the morning), usually the DS will pop right up.  It's just one of those things.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 2) Air pet invis <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You can't really be complaining about &quot;wasting mana&quot; on See Invis, can you?  I think you GAIN mana from casting that spell.  This is not an issue.  The only real problem with the air pet casting invis is that, since pets are now non-aggro, it really isn't necessary for them to do this anymore.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 3) I know I spoke about this before, but I feel it shoudl be stressed again and was wondering what everyone else's opinions about this was...Why...why why why do our pets still disappear when we go LD?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Part game mechanics, part role-playing.  Our pets are technically &quot;summoned&quot;, so when we die/go LD, we supposedly lose the concentration needed to keep a pet in this realm...  or some role-playing junk like that.  It can be a pain, but for mages it really isn't a big deal considering the relatively cheap cost of our pets compared to shaman/necro pets.<br>
